  News 

MARKET’S REACTION TO CONAGRA’S HQ ANNOUNCEMENT IS POSITIVE BUT ‘MUTED’
Omaha World Herald, October 2, 2015 – Chad Clauser comments on the market’s response to ConAgra’s announcement to move headquarters



NEAR-ZERO INTEREST RATE’S TIME MAY BE UP
Omaha World Herald, September 14, 2015 – Tom Sudyka comments on the possibility of an interest rate change by the Federal Reserve and the need for investors to stay focused on the long-term.



WALL ST WEEK AHEAD-WAGE INCREASES IN FOCUS AHEAD OF RETAIL EARNINGS
Reuters, May 8, 2015 – Tom Sudyka comments on the pressure retailers are under to raise hourly wages as unemployment rates in the U.S. give workers more leverage.



FOUR FAVORITES FOR BALANCED GROWTH
Money Show, May 6, 2015 – Tom Sudyka discusses the fundamentals of the LK Balanced Fund and provides his thoughts on four favorite long-term investments.



LAWSON KROEKER HIRES CLAUSER AS A PORTFOLIO MANAGER
April 20, 2015 – It is our pleasure to announce that Chad Clauser, CFA has joined our investment team as vice president and portfolio manager. Chad comes with a wealth of experience within the investment management industry, having spent ten successful years at several large financial institutions. Chad earned his bachelor of science in business administration from the University of Nebraska – Lincoln and in 2009 earned the Chartered Financial Analyst designation.



EUROPE VS. U.S.
CNBC, April 9, 2015 – On CNBC’s “Markets Now”, Tom Sudyka provides his insight on a couple stock picks.



GLOBAL ECONOMY DECELERATING
CNBC, March 11, 2015 – Tom Sudyka shares his opinion on whether or not there is an alternative to U.S. equities.



ATTEMPT TO FORTIFY YOUR PORTFOLIO
TheStreet, March 11, 2015 – In light of recent drop in energy prices, Tom Sudyka provides his insight on a few stock picks.



ANALYST CALLS
Bloomberg Radio, March 10, 2015 – During an interview with Bloomberg’s Michael McKee, Tom Sudyka discusses the Balanced Fund and the market.



SELLING AN ADVISORY PRACTICE MAY TAKE TIME TO ACHIEVE
Investor’s Business Daily, February 26, 2015 – Tom Sudyka says that acquiring the next generation of advisers is a big issue for the industry. “You may want a nice continual flow and continuity for your clients.”



BALANCED WITH SELECTIVITY
Ticker, January 19, 2015 – Proponents of a balanced strategy, Bruce Van Kooten and Tom Sudyka, they discuss the strategy and investment process of the LK Balanced Fund during this Q&A interview. They believe that most investors need a balance in their financial life and that a balanced product tends to keep investors involved in the market in times of distress without sacrificing return.



TOP GLOBAL INVESTMENTS: EUROPE, DISNEY AND MORE
CNBC, January 15, 2015 – Tom Sudyka thinks the stronger dollar will continue and prefers investing in the U.S. He comments on a few of his preferred stocks.



LAWSON KROEKER HIRES BEDLAN AS A PORTFOLIO MANAGER
January 9, 2015 – It is our pleasure to announce that Nick Bedlan has joined our investment team as vice president and portfolio manager. Nick brings over 13 years of experience and a track record of success in the investment industry. A Nebraska native, he earned his bachelor of science in business administration from Nebraska Wesleyan University and is a Certified Financial Planner.



TAKING STOCK: VAN KOOTEN ON STOCKS FOR 2015
Bloomberg Radio, December 23, 2014 – Bruce Van Kooten talks with Carol Massar about the LK Balanced Fund strategy, providing his perspective on a mix of stocks and bonds. He also comments on a few stocks.



10 INVESTING STRATEGIES TO LAST A LIFETIME
US News & World Report, January 14, 2015 – Investing requires a balance, says Tom Sudyka. He suggests that investors invest in what they can understand.



WHITE SWAN VS BLACK SWAN
CNBC, November 14, 2014 – Regarding the possibility of losing market share to index tracking funds, Tom Sudyka believes it’s better to focus on investing for the long term, owning high quality companies for the long term, and looking through the short-term volatility.



INVESTORS SEARCH FOR CLARITY
CNBC’s Power Lunch, October 8, 2014 – As stocks struggle for direction, Tom Sudyka discusses nervousness in markets as earnings season approaches.



WHY WOULD THEY SELL THIS STOCK TO US AT THIS PRICE?
Forbes, October 16, 2014 – Tom Sudyka sits down for a Q&A feature with Wally Forbes.



A Fundamentally Focused, Long-term Investment Philosophy

The Wall Street Transcript, September 29, 2014 – Bruce Van Kooten and Tom Sudyka discuss their long-term investment focus.



Seeking balance: a Bottoms-up Strategy
MoneyShow, August 25, 2014 – Tom Sudyka discusses the bottom-up approach of Lawson Kroeker with Steven Halpern. He believes that focusing on individual securities and analysis positions portfolios to handle rising rates or deflation.



LK’s Sudyka Says Midwest Does Not Focus on ‘Chatter’

Bloomberg Radio, July 30, 2014 – During Bloomberg Radio’s “Taking Stock” segment, Tom Sudyka discusses the markets and looking for value with Bloomberg’s Pimm Fox and Carol Massar.



Lawson Kroeker Investment Management Named To Financial Times’ Top 300 RIA List

Omaha, Neb, June 27, 2014 – Lawson Kroeker Investment Management announced today its inclusion among the 2014 Financial Times Top 300 Registered Investment Advisers. The firm joins financial advisory firms from 37 states and Washington D.C. in being selected to the list.
