Brookfield Asset Management Inc (BAM) Ownership Increased by Lawson Kroeker Investment Management Inc/ne
July 11, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Brookfield Asset Management Inc (NYSE:BAM). 
 Lawson Kroeker Investment Management Inc/ne raised its investment in Brookfield Asset Management Inc shares by 0.3%  in its quarterly SEC filing.  Its position was valued at $11,493,000 an increase of $838,000 according to the filing. 
 The following firms have also recently changed their position in BAM.   Bank Of Montreal /can/ reduced its holdings by selling 547 shares a decrease of 67.5% as of 06/30/2017. Bank Of Montreal /can/ now controls 263 shares valued at $10,000. The value of the position overall is down by 66.7%. Davenport & Co LLC downsized its stake by shedding 22,988 shares a decrease of 0.5%. Davenport & Co LLC controls 4,376,767 shares with a value of $150,784,000. The total value of its holdings increased 1.4%.
 Hexavest Inc. grew its position by buying 10,540 shares an increase of 1.6% in the quarter. Hexavest Inc. now holds 677,772 shares worth $26,559,000. The total value of its holdings increased 9.6%.
  Equity analyst Keefe Bruyette &amp; Woods added BAM to its research portfolio by announcing an initial rating of “Outperform” and a price target of $41.00. On October 16 the company was upgraded from “Sector Perform” to “Sector Outperform” in an announcement from CIBC.





 BMO Capital both upgraded the stock and raised the price target on September 30 changing the price target from $38.00 to $40.00 and raising the rating from “Market Perform” to “Outperform”. On September 30 the stock rating was upgraded to “Outperform” from “Market Perform” and a price target of $40.00 was set in a statement from BMO Capital.
 Credit Suisse started coverage with a rating of “Neutral” and establishing a price target of $56.00. On August 14 CIBC left the company rating at “Sector Perform” and raised the price target  to $47.50 from $44.00.
 The company is so far trading up since yesterday’s close of $38.88.  Brookfield Asset Management Inc also recently declared a dividend for shareholders that was paid on Friday the 30th of June 2017.  The dividend was $0.130 per share for the quarter or $0.52 on an annualized basis.  This dividend represents a yield of $1.56.  The ex-dividend date was Monday the 29th of May 2017. 
 It is currently trading at $38.96 just a bit higher than $38.25, the stock’s 50 day moving average and marginally over the 200 day moving average of $36.26.  The 50 day moving average went up $0.71 or +1.87% whereas the 200 day moving average was up $2.70 or +7.43%. 
 The company’s P/E ratio is 31.24 and the market value is 37.35B.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $1.25 and is projected to be $1.31 for the current year with 958,578,000 shares currently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted to be $0.27 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $2.07. 






