Leggett & Platt, Incorporated (NYSE:LEG) Position Held by Lawson Kroeker Investment Management Inc. NE

Posted by Toi Williams on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 

Lawson Kroeker Investment Management Inc. NE held its position in shares of Leggett & Platt, Incorporated (NYSE:LEG) during the second quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 9,600 shares of the company’s stock at the end of the second quarter. Lawson Kroeker Investment Management Inc. NE’s holdings in Leggett & Platt, were worth $504,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
A number of other institutional investors have also recently made changes to their positions in LEG. Berkshire Asset Management LLC PA increased its position in shares of Leggett & Platt, by 1.5% in the first quarter. Berkshire Asset Management LLC PA now owns 452,456 shares of the company’s stock worth $22,768,000 after buying an additional 6,515 shares in the last quarter. Gotham Asset Management LLC increased its position in shares of Leggett & Platt, by 270.6% in the first quarter. Gotham Asset Management LLC now owns 157,645 shares of the company’s stock worth $7,933,000 after buying an additional 115,102 shares in the last quarter. Pegasus Partners Ltd. boosted its stake in Leggett & Platt, by 6.7% in the fourth quarter. Pegasus Partners Ltd. now owns 44,968 shares of the company’s stock worth $2,198,000 after buying an additional 2,807 shares during the last quarter. Russell Investments Group Ltd. bought a new stake in Leggett & Platt, during the fourth quarter worth approximately $3,009,000. Finally, Huntington National Bank boosted its stake in Leggett & Platt, by 0.8% in the first quarter. Huntington National Bank now owns 9,101 shares of the company’s stock worth $458,000 after buying an additional 69 shares during the last quarter. 72.09% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 




Shares of Leggett & Platt, Incorporated (NYSE LEG) traded up 0.06% on Friday, hitting $52.60. 200,394 shares of the stock were exchanged. The company has a 50-day moving average price of $52.59 and a 200 day moving average price of $50.74. The company has a market cap of $6.96 billion, a PE ratio of 19.15 and a beta of 1.01. Leggett & Platt, Incorporated has a 12 month low of $44.02 and a 12 month high of $54.97. 


 Get Leggett & Platt Incorporated alerts:



Leggett & Platt, (NYSE:LEG) last issued its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, April 27th. The company reported $0.62 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.59 by $0.03. The firm had revenue of $960.30 million during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $958.98 million. Leggett & Platt, had a net margin of 10.14% and a return on equity of 31.91%. The business’s revenue was up 2.3% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period last year, the company earned $0.63 earnings per share. Equities analysts forecast that Leggett & Platt, Incorporated will post $2.63 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Friday, July 14th. Stockholders of record on Thursday, June 15th were issued a dividend of $0.36 per share. This is a boost from Leggett & Platt,’s previous quarterly dividend of $0.34. This represents a $1.44 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 2.74%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend was Tuesday, June 13th. Leggett & Platt,’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is currently 52.36%. 
WARNING: “Leggett & Platt, Incorporated (NYSE:LEG) Position Held by Lawson Kroeker Investment Management Inc. NE” was first posted by BNB Daily and is owned by of BNB Daily. If you are viewing this report on another domain, it was illegally copied and reposted in violation of U.S. & international copyright & trademark legislation. The correct version of this report can be read at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/21/lawson-kroeker-investment-management-inc-ne-has-504000-stake-in-leggett-platt-incorporated-nyseleg-updated.html. 
A number of equities research analysts have commented on the stock. Gabelli assumed coverage on shares of Leggett & Platt, in a report on Wednesday, June 21st. They issued a “hold” rating and a $53.00 price target for the company. Zacks Investment Research cut shares of Leggett & Platt, from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Monday, May 15th. Piper Jaffray Companies restated a “buy” rating and issued a $59.00 price target on shares of Leggett & Platt, in a report on Friday, July 14th. Stifel Nicolaus raised their price target on shares of Leggett & Platt, from $48.00 to $52.00 and gave the stock a “hold” rating in a report on Monday, April 3rd. Finally, BidaskClub upgraded shares of Leggett & Platt, from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating in a report on Saturday, June 17th. Seven analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating, two have assigned a buy rating and two have given a strong buy rating to the stock. The company currently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus price target of $55.57.
In related news, Director Joseph W. Mcclanathan sold 5,715 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction dated Monday, May 1st. The shares were sold at an average price of $52.91, for a total transaction of $302,380.65. Following the transaction, the director now directly owns 32,314 shares in the company, valued at $1,709,733.74. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which can be accessed through the SEC website. Also, SVP Scott S. Douglas sold 5,000 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, May 3rd. The stock was sold at an average price of $53.26, for a total transaction of $266,300.00. Following the transaction, the senior vice president now owns 36,133 shares in the company, valued at $1,924,443.58. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders have sold 46,320 shares of company stock valued at $2,477,652 over the last quarter. Corporate insiders own 1.78% of the company’s stock. 
About Leggett & Platt,
Leggett & Platt, Incorporated is a manufacturer that conceives, designs and produces a range of engineered components and products found in homes, offices and automobiles. The Company operates in four segments: Residential Furnishings, Commercial Products, Industrial Materials and Specialized Products. 

 
